        "By the end of this tutorial, you‚Äôll learn how to create your first homepage in Webflow and leave with a solid understanding of how to build powerful websites in Webflow ‚Äî by visually coding HTML and CSS.",
      name: "Behind the feature: building multi-account",
      "post-body":
        '<p>There‚Äôs a lot of hype around the <a href="http://google.com">no code movement</a> ‚Äî a wave of technologies that allow us to build software without code. But code is at the internet‚Äôs core. It‚Äôs not about the absence of using it to build websites and apps. This movement is actually focused on making it easier (and faster) to code ‚Äî by making it visual. Meaning, you just design and platforms like Webflow write the code for you.</p><p>If you approach Webflow with the mindset of designing, based on the <strong>fundamentals</strong> code, <em>you‚Äôll be able to learn it quickly</em>. And on top of that, you might end up learning how to code as well.</p><figure class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-center" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="center"><div><img src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/5ff21113877dd79ed7913b57/607dc680e065c836f563201a_stacking.club.gif" loading="lazy" width="auto" height="auto"></div><figcaption>small image</figcaption></figure><figure class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:1404px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="1404px"><div><img src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/5ff21113877dd79ed7913b57/607d5bcd158fffbdeaf54702_Stacking.png" loading="lazy" width="auto" height="auto"></div><figcaption>large image</figcaption></figure><h3>What is Webflow?</h3><p>Webflow is a design and web development tool, ecommerce, CMS, and hosting platform. Each aspect of the platform is represented by a particular product/feature set:</p><ul><li>Bullet one</li><li>Bullet two</li><li>Bullet three</li></ul><h4>The designer</h4><p>There‚Äôs a lot of hype around the no code movement ‚Äî a wave of technologies that allow us to build software without code. But code is at the internet‚Äôs core. It‚Äôs not about the absence of using it to build websites and apps. This movement is actually focused on making it easier (and faster) to code ‚Äî by making it visual. Meaning, you just design and platforms like Webflow write the code for you.</p><h3>Embedding stuff</h3><h4>Tweets</h4><div></div><h4>Code</h4><p>Code can be embedded the hacky way using a h6 tag:</p><h6>&lt;p&gt;hello&lt;/p&gt;</h6><p>But you can also embed gists:</p><div></div><h5>Blockquotes</h5><blockquote>Stripe, Apple Pay, Paypal, or Google Pay, while also extending your stores capabilities with various integrations.</blockquote><p>If you approach Webflow with the mindset of designing, based on the fundamentals code, you‚Äôll be able to learn it quickly. And on top of that, you might end up learning how to code as well.<br></p>',
